Three people were yesterday confirmed dead when a helicopter crashed into a private residential build- ing located in 16A Salvation Road, Opebi area of Ikeja, Lagos State. LEADERSHIP Weekend gathered that the privately operated helicopter crashed at about 12:15, leaving two dead and the third occupant in coma. A 90-year-old woman identified as Mrs. Adepe- ju Johnson who escaped death by the whiskers said she was devastated by the impact of the crash. Confirming the accident, the director-general, Lagos State Emergency Manage- ment Agency, (LASEMA), Dr. Femi Oke-Osannyinto- lu, said two people died in the helicopter that crashed into a building at Salvation Road, Opebi, Ikeja area of Lagos. According to him, three people were on board the aircraft when it crashed. He said the agency received distress calls concerning a privately operat- ed helicopter that crashed into 16 A Salvation Road, Opebi, Ikeja and he immediately activated the emergency response plan. According to him, one person was in the intensive care unit at the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital, LASUTH, while the two dead bodies had been deposited at the mortuary. “The helicopter was carrying three (3) people, one is in the intensive care unit at the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital while the other two were killed on impact and their bodies have  been deposited in a mortuary. “We are on top of challenges, especially crowd control. Operation is ongoing and updates will follow,” he said. It was further gathered that the helicopter is said to belong to Quorum Aviation.